            "answer_text": "Very far ideologically. The fundamental Stoic belief is that it is the purpose of life to act in accordance with Nature. They definitely believed in meaning and purpose to things. A certain form of apathy might result from nihilism, but Stoic lack of emotion is because virtue is regarded as the only good, vice is regarded as the only evil, and it is mistaken to allow anything else to affect your emotions. It's not because they believed that nothing matters, etc. ",
